summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of computer brands based on their share of a survey sample and customer repeat purchase percentage. Dell leads with the largest share of the survey sample at 27%, followed closely by HP/Compaq at 26%. Toshiba and Apple each represent 10% and 9% of the sample, respectively, with Toshiba and Apple showing identical repeat purchase rates of 24%. Gateway accounts for 5% of the sample with a 28% repeat rate. IBM/Lenovo has the smallest sample share at 3%, and notably, the lowest repeat purchase rate at 10% (marked with an asterisk). The structure is comparative, highlighting market presence and customer loyalty across different brands.
